   {:e #blake3 "80381738812489a24b3e699050a61d34f8101dc210383c5be8c09088310c8824" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: DEFECT-005 from Session 044 audit. The three frontier tests (test_frontier_explore, test_frontier_deepen, test_frontier_bridge) each test one kind in isolation. No test creates a store where all three candidate types return results simultaneously and verifies winner selection.\n\nRATIONALE: After S045-Q1 applies score normalization, we need a test that exercises the full comparison path. An isolated test can't catch normalization regressions because each test only has one candidate type (which always normalizes to 1.0).\n\nAPPROACH: Create test_frontier_all_three_candidates:\n1. Build store with schema.\n2. Add 5 :pkg/* entities with composition edges, mark 2 as explored — triggers Explore candidates.\n3. Add a concept with high variance (>=0.8) and >=3 members — triggers Deepen candidate.\n4. Add two concepts with disjoint membership sets (>=2 each) — triggers Bridge candidate.\n5. Call frontier_recommendation().\n6. Assert result is Some. Assert the winning kind is the one with the highest NORMALIZED score.\n7. Verify that all three FrontierKind variants appear in the pre-sort candidate list (may need to refactor frontier_recommendation to expose candidates for testing, or use a helper that returns all candidates).\n\nACCEPTANCE: (A) Test constructs a store triggering all 3 candidate types. (B) Test passes with normalized scoring. (C) If normalization is removed, test may fail (depending on scale relationship).\n\nDEPENDS-ON: S045-Q1 (normalization must be in place for this test to be meaningful).\n\nCONSIDERATIONS: May need to expose a frontier_candidates() function that returns the full Vec<FrontierRec> before winner selection, to make assertions about all three types. This is a minor API addition, not a refactor. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs (tests module)" :op :assert}
